commit.message: update NEWS file for 1.6.2
Close bug #4
Finish fiddling with the URL indicator text
ioctl.ph is not often installed; do a better job of loading modules for term size detection
Update NEWS file for 1.6.1
Expand context to fill the width of the terminal (bump version to 1.6.1)
fix tab-vs-space issue
fix issue #3 - thanks chdiza!
fix tab
document COMMAND/escape behavior change
allow more things to be unescaped in the case that we can avoid the shell (i.e. when COMMAND does not contain %s)

Expand environment variables in COMMAND (to avoid relying on the shell) and attempt to detect whether this is something simple (and can fully avoid going to the shell) or not based on whether %s is used.
add RAW_RESERVED to sample config
add RAW_RESERVED option to toggle between aggressive escaping and non-aggressive escaping (fix for Issue #1)
fix Issue #2 via patch from christiwald - Thanks!!! Also, fix dependency on MIME::QuotedPrint

Merge branch 'master' of https://code.google.com/p/extracturl

Conflicts:
	extract_url.pl
find protocol-less URLs (without URI::Find module)
config file can be specified explicitly; and $HOME is now optional
detect URLs that do not necessarily have protocol identifiers, but do have well-known suffixes (.com, .net, .org, and .gov), because those are often clickable in many clients
use a cleaner way of detecting optional modules
Add a way to force quoted-printable decoding of plain text
correct the version number (thanks Greg Novak!)
sample config file (thanks Horia Racoviceanu!)
uncomplicate input handling (eliminate use of IO::Scalar in favor of doing it all in-core)
allow non-stdin inputs
create the --text option
fix treating input as text
useful for debian packaging
